    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows the top view of two diagrams labeled Figure 1 and Figure 2. Each diagram shows a horizontal rod of length L with a downward force F sub 0 applied to its right end. On each rod, an axis is marked by a dot. In figure 1, the axis is located at the center of the rod. In figure 2 the axis is located at a distance of one third L from the left end of the rod.\" src=\"/images/be88e45f07e83fc64c8e069f41fc4cf9.svg\"></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A force with magnitude <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub 0\"><math alttext=\"F sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span> is applied to the right end of a uniform rod of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"M\"><math alttext=\"M\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>M</mi></math></span></span> and length <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"L\"><math alttext=\"L\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>L</mi></math></span></span> that lies on top of a horizontal surface, as shown in Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>. The rod is free to rotate with negligible friction about an axis through its center and perpendicular to the plane of the surface. The rotational inertia of the rod about the axis is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"One twelfth M L squared\"><math alttext=\"One twelfth M L squared\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>12</mn></mfrac><mi>M</mi><msup><mi>L</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math></span></span>, and the rod’s initial angular acceleration is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"alpha sub 1\"><math alttext=\"alpha sub 1\" display=\"inli